Explanation:

The user enters a new note in the text field of the SPA.
The user clicks the Save button.
The SPA checks the user's authentication status.
  If authenticated, it proceeds to create a new note object.
  If not authenticated, it shows the login page.
The SPA checks the network connection.
  If connected, it sends a POST request to the server with the new note data.
  If not connected, an error is shown to the user.
On a successful server response, the SPA updates its interface with the new note.
  If there's an error, it is shown to the user.
